        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Extended Description</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f082981002">air dryer and heated drain valve circuits</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>The heated drain valve (9526) and air dryer (9257) receive battery voltage from a 20 amp fuse (4017)
                in the engine power distribution center through the air dryer/drain valve relay (4016). When the key
                switch is placed in the start or ignition position the air dryer/drain valve relay is charged from fuse
                F23 in the fuse block (1011). Ground for the heated drain valve and the air dryer is supplied from
                chassis ground.
            </para>
            <para>The Haldex drain valve (9527) is supplied power with the body builder stop light relay and the auto
                drain valve relay (1018) are charged. The auto drain valve relay is charged from fuse F19. Ground for
                the Haldex drain valve (9527) is supplied from chassis ground.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
